===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[πεντάγραμμον]]'' (pentagrammon), noun form of the adjectives ''[[πεντάγραμμος]]'' (pentagrammos) and ''[[πεντέγραμμος]]'' (pentegrammos), five-lined, having five lines.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[shape]] of a five-pointed [[star]] constructed of [[five]] intersecting lines meeting at the vertices, such that a central pentagon and five surrounding isoceles triangles are formed; often with [[magic]]al connotations.
# The shape of a five-pointed [[star]].
#{{mathematics}} a 5/2 [[star polygon]]

